Managing Complexity: As software grows, maintaining code readability and scalability becomes challenging.

Solution: Use modular design, adhere to coding standards, and employ design patterns.
Dealing with Unclear Requirements: Ambiguities in requirements can lead to rework and project delays.

Solution: Engage in continuous communication with stakeholders and use Agile methodologies for iterative development.
Time Constraints: Deadlines can lead to rushed work and technical debt.

Solution: Prioritize tasks, automate repetitive processes, and manage time effectively using tools like Trello or Jira.
